6.20	Cry_(Faith_Hill_album)	Cry (Faith Hill album)	Cry is the fifth studio album by American country music singer Faith Hill. It was released October 15, 2002 via Warner Bros. Records selling 472,486 copies in its first week, a career best for Hill. The album was intended as a crossover project for her, and although three of its singles were released to country radio, none reached Top Ten. The title track and "One" were both Adult Contemoporary hits, however. It went on to sell 4 million copies worldwide. Hill has publicly stated that, of all the albums she has recorded, Cry is her favorite. Cry also hit #179 on the Billboard Top 200 albums of the decade 2000-2009.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/79/Faith_Hill_-_Cry.jpg/220px-Faith_Hill_-_Cry.jpg
